The paper deals with the problem of learning reward functions for autonomous robots, which is a common topic in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). The proposed method involves integrating human demonstrations and preferences, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper discusses the efficiency and effectiveness of the proposed method, which is relevant to the field of control systems (cs.SY).
